PrecisEnactment of the OATH OR SOLEMN AFFIRMATION OF OFFICE RULES (IMMIGRATION AND REFUGEE BOARD) which formalize the practice of administering an Oath of Office or Solemn Affirmation to all new members of the Board, except members of the Immigration Division who are appointed under the Public Service Employment Act, effective June 28, 2002.
RegistrationRegistration: SOR/ 2002-0231 Publication Date: 2002-07-03
Attachments
precis:
Enactment of the OATH OR SOLEMN AFFIRMATION OF OFFICE RULES (IMMIGRATION
AND REFUGEE BOARD) which formalize the practice of administering an Oath of
Office or Solemn Affirmation to all new members of the Board, except
members of the Immigration Division who are appointed under the Public
Service Employment Act, effective June 28, 2002.
